## Decisions Made
- Deterministic fallback over glob: on-stop.sh fallback now derives the expected team name from the current repo root instead of picking the first atelier-* match, preventing cross-project misidentification.
- 8-char hash prefix: Increased from 4 to 8 hex chars to materially reduce collision risk across repos with similar basenames.
- TeamCreate/TeamDelete as canonical names: These are the actual Claude Code tool names; foundations.md informal names (spawnTeam/cleanup) updated for consistency.
- Safety guard on destructive fallback: rm -rf in documentation now requires non-empty team_name with atelier- prefix validation before deletion.

## Problems Encountered
- CodeRabbit flagged that the atelier-* glob fallback in on-stop.sh could select a different project's team directory when multiple atelier-* dirs exist: resolved by computing the expected name deterministically.

## Constraints Identified
- Hash derivation must stay in sync: on-stop.sh fallback, SKILL.md team name derivation, and any future code that resolves team names must use identical sanitization and hash length (currently 8 chars of sha256).

